    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-02-25T08:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-02-25T08:00:00-05:00" n="872"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d872">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">681.003/156: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Spain</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bowers</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Madrid</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-02-25T13:00:00+00:00"
                            >February 25, 1935—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received February 26—9:15 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>15. Department’s 15, February 21, 6 p.m. Informed by Foreign Office that matter
                    had been referred to Spanish High Commissioner at Tetuan and until a reply was
                    received it could not make a reply. Foreign Office stated it was pressing for an
                    answer and expected a reply within 10 days. Attributed delay to indifference of
                    High Commissioner to our recognition of the Spanish Zone unless question of
                    capitulations was included in agreement.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bowers</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
